                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc>
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support><p>A funerary altar, somewhat eroded on all faces. Quadrangular in form, with triple moulding at the top of the main block, surmounted by scrolls on each side with a central horn, and a raised square block on the upper surface behind the horn. The front face of the altar has relief designs on the lower half, which may relate to milling, and a relief form of a tabula ansata on the upper part, which contains a Greek funerary inscription. The right side carries further relief designs showing tools associated with crafts.</p>
                                    <material ana="#material.stone.limestone" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/66.html">limestone</material>
                                    <objectType ana="#object.altar" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/29.html">altar</objectType>
                                    <dimensions><!-- Orsi's measurements -->
